cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CE 

The paper discusses a method of user expertise modelization in crowdsourcing platforms, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as well as cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of belief functions also suggests a connection to statistical learning (cs.SD) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
